Trees in Cassandra. Really.

1) Transform any Java object to a Tree

```java
		ComplexObject complexObject = new ComplexObject(); // here's your object
		AnnotatedObjectSerializer<ComplexObject> serializer = new AnnotatedObjectSerializer<ComplexObject>(); // the serializer for it

		MapSerializer<HashMap> mapWithGenericsSerializer = new MapSerializer<HashMap>(); // this is to serialize generic maps. No custom serializer needed ( but definitely possible ) for ComplexObject
		mapWithGenericsSerializer.setKeyGenericType(String.class);
		mapWithGenericsSerializer.setValueGenericType(Integer.class);
		
		SerializerRegistry.getInstance().register(mapWithGenericsSerializer, ComplexObject.class.getField("mapWithGenericsTypeField")); // register the above serializer specifically for the generic map field in question
		
		Node serializedComplexObject = serializer.serialize(ComplexObject.class, complexObject); // go!

```